replyContent: Dear Pavel, I received many similar reports from users regarding Windows Firewall. You can have the firewall enabled and add an exception for Java Runtime to be able to use SuperBeam. I'm working on a new update for PC app which will automate this for you.

Though I buy a lot of "stuff", usually I'm too lazy to review my purchases.  Not this time.  Maybe my habits are unusual but I typically buy to solve a particular problem. So at this point I can only offer my opinion specifically about SuperBeam Pro's video transfer functionality.  My particular "problem" was getting 63 videos off my Samsung S6 and onto my computer. I tried a number of approaches and had settled on using simple Bluetooth when the failed transfers and mobility limits (can't wander more than a spitting distance from my computer...), proved too discouraging and finally forced me to "learn" something new.  Like: "What the heck is Wi-Fi Direct?"  After reading just enough about the subject to be dangerous I did what I typically do which is: Go to Google Play, search for try out the highest rated solutions what looks like it might work.  I tried SuperBeam first and HOLY COW was it fast!   e.g.: A 100 MB video via Bluetooth: About 10 minutes. The same video via SuperBeam: less than a minute!  Upgrading to Pro: A 12.6 GB zip of all my videos: 20 +/- minutes!  With these results, why try anything else?  I couldn't be more pleased!  THANKS SuperBeam!

replyContent: On KitKat, apps are no longer be able create, modify or delete files and directories on external SD card. This applies to all apps that manipulate files (like file managers), and SuperBeam is not an exception. We are still looking for a feasible workaround (although so far, root access is the only way). Thank you for your feedback.

content: This app has the fastest file transfer speeds, upto 11MB/s. However few issues with it:  - Connectivity was not consistent. Somtimes took upto 4 tries to transfer one batch of 50MB.  - Upon completion, it doesn't show if the transfer was successful or failure. You have to check on the other device to know.  - With PC, when it fails, it just says 'Unknown error' and doesn't offer retry option.  - Upon completion, pressing back key closes the app rather than going back to the opened directory.  - The notification doesn't show the progress so you have to have the app open to see the progress.

I was okay using file Explorer on PC thru USB and Dropbox, G -drive for file transfers until discovering SuperBeam. It's so much easier to transfer files between multiple devices. Unlocked Pro version let me connect to PC as well as transfer entire folder. Much easier to use than Airdroid, which I abandoned long ago. The only suggestion I'd give is to setup a unique name for each device to avoid scanning barcode all the time.

This app was just what I was looking for. With its hotspot mode it even works with devices that do not support direct mode. It can also stand up a custom web server to transfer files to a device that does not have the app installed. If you have your wifi turned off by default, this app will temporarily enable it just to do the transfer. The author has taken time to get this app working really well, it shows in its quality when you use it.
Very useful
I have been able to consistently transfer files around 30mbps. 9gb took about 30 minutes.

Much further! If you want to move files or folders, big or small. Then this is the app you need. It does it very fast and hassle free (I use it a lot and it has never corrupted a single file) which already puts it head and shoulders above its competitors but the extra little touches like being able to have   the folder you're copying across to another device be received as a handily compressed zip file is one of the many things that make this app an absolute must have. I recommend it to all my friends and even some random people I walk past in the street.

replyContent: Dear Yousuf, thanks for the suggestion. Currently, SuperBeam renames duplicate files by adding an underscore followed by a number to the file name. I will make the option to override existing files available on the next update. Stay tuned!

replyContent: SuperBeam 3.0.2 is up right now. You may find the share APK button on the main screen (on top menu). Now you can share the APK with any app that supports file sharing (like Gmail and DropBox). Sending via Bluetooth might not work, as some devices refuse to receive APK files over Bluetooth.
